   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# N-gram Explorer\\n\",\"**NLP Project 14 of 100**\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Project Overview\\n\",\"Build unigram, bigram, and trigram features and compare their impact on text classification.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"1. Understand n-gram features and their role in NLP.\\n\",\"2. Compare uni/bi/trigram feature spaces.\\n\",\"3. Measure impact on classification performance.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Why This Matters\\n\",\"N-grams capture word context and phrases that single words miss (e.g., 'not good' vs 'good').\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\",\\\"numpy\\\",\\\"matplotlib\\\",\\\"seaborn\\\",\\\"scikit-learn\\\",\\\"datasets\\\"]:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,\\\"-m\\\",\\\"pip\\\",\\\"install\\\",\\\"-q\\\",pkg])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\nfrom sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer, CountVectorizer\\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\nfrom sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score\\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\nSEED = 42; np.random.seed(SEED)\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"from datasets import load_dataset\\nds = load_dataset('imdb', split='train').shuffle(seed=SEED).select(range(5000))\\ndf = ds.to_pandas()\\nX_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df['text'], df['label'], test_size=0.2, random_state=SEED)\\nprint(f'Train: {len(X_train)}, Test: {len(X_test)}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## N-gram Comparison Experiment\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"configs = {'Unigram (1,1)': (1,1), 'Bigram (1,2)': (1,2), 'Trigram (1,3)': (1,3), 'Bigram only (2,2)': (2,2)}\\nresults = []\\nfor name, ngram in configs.items():\\n    tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=15000, ngram_range=ngram)\\n    X_tr = tfidf.fit_transform(X_train); X_te = tfidf.transform(X_test)\\n    lr = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=SEED)\\n    lr.fit(X_tr, y_train); y_pred = lr.predict(X_te)\\n    results.append({'N-gram': name, 'Accuracy': accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n                    'F1': f1_score(y_test, y_pred), 'Features': X_tr.shape[1]})\\n\\nresults_df = pd.DataFrame(results)\\nprint(results_df.to_string(index=False))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,5))\\nresults_df.plot(x='N-gram',y=['Accuracy','F1'],kind='bar',ax=ax)\\nax.set_title('N-gram Impact on Classification'); ax.set_ylim(0.8,0.95)\\nax.tick_params(axis='x',rotation=30); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Top N-grams by Class\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=10000, ngram_range=(2,2))\\nX_all = tfidf.fit_transform(df['text'])\\nterms = tfidf.get_feature_names_out()\\nfor label, name in [(1,'Positive'),(0,'Negative')]:\\n    mask = df['label'] == label\\n    avg = X_all[mask].mean(axis=0).A1\\n    top = avg.argsort()[-10:][::-1]\\n    print(f'\\\\nTop bigrams for {name}: {[terms[i] for i in top]}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Bigrams (1,2) provide the best balance** of context and vocabulary size.\\n\",\"- **Trigrams add diminishing returns** and increase sparsity.\\n\",\"- **Bigram-only features miss individual word signals.**\\n\",\"- **For sentiment, bigrams capture negation patterns** ('not good', 'very bad').\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
    " \"metadata\":{\"kernelspec\":{\"display_name\":\"Python 3\",\"language\":\"python\",\"name\":\"python3\"},\"language_info\":{\"name\":\"python\",\"version\":\"3.11.0\"}},\n",
